# Complete Repository Audit — Functional Bug Report

A comprehensive audit of the SRSMA Student Dashboard codebase, identifying functional bugs especially in edge cases across authentication, data processing, API routes, and UI components.

---

## Critical Bugs 🔴

### BUG-01: Notification system uses `student name` as key, but notifications are sent to `student name` — retrieval uses `session.user.name` which can mismatch

**Files:** [notifications route](file:///c:/Users/panga/OneDrive/Desktop/Seva/SRSMA/SRSMADashBoard/src/app/api/student/notifications/route.ts#L13), [performance route](file:///c:/Users/panga/OneDrive/Desktop/Seva/SRSMA/SRSMADashBoard/src/app/api/data/performance/route.ts#L53), [upload route](file:///c:/Users/panga/OneDrive/Desktop/Seva/SRSMA/SRSMADashBoard/src/app/api/data/upload/route.ts#L47)

When marks are uploaded/updated, notifications are sent using `student.name` (the student's display name). But in the notification retrieval endpoint, we fetch with `session.user.name!`. The `!` non-null assertion is dangerous — if `session.user.name` is somehow null/undefined, this will pass `undefined` to the DB query instead of failing gracefully.

**More importantly:** The `addNotification` call uses the **student name from the performance data** (e.g. `"Ravi Kumar"`), but `markNotificationAsReadById` and `getUnreadNotifications` use `session.user.name`. If the student's name in performance_marks doesn't exactly match `users.name` (case, whitespace), notifications will be **orphaned** — created but never retrievable.

**Edge case:** If a teacher renames a student via `updateStudentDetails`, the `performance_marks.student_name` is updated but **existing notifications** with the old name are NOT migrated (only `notifications.username` is updated in `updateStudentDetails`). However, future notifications from performance edits will use the new `student_name`, while the notification lookup uses `session.user.name` which comes from `users.name`. If these diverge, notifications break.

