### BUG-02: `updateStudentDetails` cannot clear email — empty string treated as "keep existing"

**File:** [db.ts#L254-L261](file:///c:/Users/panga/OneDrive/Desktop/Seva/SRSMA/SRSMADashBoard/src/lib/db.ts#L254-L261)

```typescript
const emailVal = email !== undefined ? email : null;
// ...
email = CASE WHEN ${emailVal}::text IS NOT NULL THEN ${emailVal}::text ELSE email END
```

The comment says *"so that empty strings can overwrite existing values (allowing the teacher to clear them)"*, but the SQL `CASE WHEN ${emailVal}::text IS NOT NULL` will be true for empty string `""`, so empty string **does** overwrite. But if `email` is passed as `null` explicitly, the CASE falls through to `ELSE email`, keeping the existing value. This is confusing but **technically works for empty string**. However, the real problem is that passing `email: null` (meaning "I want to set it to null") is impossible — it always keeps the old value. There's no way to **actually clear** the email to NULL in the database.

