### BUG-03: `editClass` inconsistently updates `users.class` vs `performance_marks.class_name`

**File:** [db.ts#L406-L422](file:///c:/Users/panga/OneDrive/Desktop/Seva/SRSMA/SRSMADashBoard/src/lib/db.ts#L406-L422)

```typescript
const newClassRaw = newClassName.replace(/^Class_/i, '');
await sql`UPDATE users SET class = ${newClassRaw} WHERE class = ANY(${oldClassRawArray})`;
await sql`UPDATE performance_marks SET class_name = ${newClassName} WHERE class_name = ${oldClassName}`;
```

Users table stores the **raw** class value (e.g. `"12+"`), while `performance_marks` stores the **folder-style** name (e.g. `"Class_12+"`). When renaming, the users table is updated with the raw stripped value, but the performance_marks table is updated with the full `Class_` prefixed value. This is correct **only if** the old and new names both use the `Class_` prefix convention. If someone renames a class to something without `Class_` prefix, or if the DB already has inconsistent data, this will break lookups.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The function also doesn't update `teacher_mappings.class_name`, so renaming a class **orphans all teacher mappings** for that class.

