### BUG-05: `folderToExcelClassValues` doesn't handle common class name variants

**File:** [db.ts#L713-L718](file:///c:/Users/panga/OneDrive/Desktop/Seva/SRSMA/SRSMADashBoard/src/lib/db.ts#L713-L718)

```typescript
function folderToExcelClassValues(folderName: string): string[] {
    let raw = folderName.replace(/^Class_/i, '');
    const values: string[] = [raw];
    values.push(raw.toLowerCase(), raw.toUpperCase());
    return [...new Set(values)];
}
```

For `Class_12+`, this generates `["12+", "12+", "12+"]` (since `"12+".toLowerCase() === "12+"` and `"12+".toUpperCase() === "12+"`). It does NOT handle Roman numerals (`XII`, `xii`), numeric-only (`12`), or space variants (`12 +`). If any student's `class` field in the DB is stored differently (e.g. `"Class 12+"` vs `"12+"` vs `"XII"`), the lookup will fail silently.

