### BUG-08: `getMaxRollSequence` has fragile roll number parsing — can generate duplicates

**File:** [db.ts#L327-L357](file:///c:/Users/panga/OneDrive/Desktop/Seva/SRSMA/SRSMADashBoard/src/lib/db.ts#L327-L357)

The function tries to find the max roll sequence by parsing the last 2 digits. For class `Class_12+`:
- `classPrefix = "12+"`  
- It checks `roll.startsWith("12+")` but roll numbers use the format `26{classPrefix}{seq}` (e.g. `2612+01`)

The `+` in `"12+"` can cause issues with string matching. Also, if a student has a roll number that coincidentally ends with digits (e.g. transferred students with different formats), this will produce wrong maxSeq, potentially **generating a duplicate roll number** that violates a unique constraint, causing a silent failure with no error reported to the user.

