### BUG-10: `PerformanceChart` crashes on empty data array

**File:** [PerformanceChart.tsx#L16](file:///c:/Users/panga/OneDrive/Desktop/Seva/SRSMA/SRSMADashBoard/src/components/PerformanceChart.tsx#L16)

```typescript
const maxTopicLength = Math.max(...data.map(d => d.topic ? d.topic.length : 0), 10);
```

If `data` is an empty array, `Math.max(...[])` returns `-Infinity`, but the `,10` fallback saves it. However, if `data` contains items where `topic` is `undefined`, `d.topic.length` will throw. The guard `d.topic ?` only handles falsy topics. This same pattern exists in [RankTrendChart.tsx#L23](file:///c:/Users/panga/OneDrive/Desktop/Seva/SRSMA/SRSMADashBoard/src/components/RankTrendChart.tsx#L23).

