### BUG-11: `calculateRanks` has a duplicate name collision bug

**File:** [engine.ts#L20-L51](file:///c:/Users/panga/OneDrive/Desktop/Seva/SRSMA/SRSMADashBoard/src/lib/engine.ts#L20-L51)

```typescript
const rankMap = new Map<string, number>();
// ...
rankMap.set(student.name, ...);
```

If two students have the **exact same name** (which is plausible in Indian schools, e.g. two "Ravi Kumar" in the same class), the `Map` key collision means the second student's rank **overwrites** the first. The `rankedStudents.map` then assigns the same rank to both, which may be wrong if they have different marks. The root issue is using `name` as a unique key when names are not unique.

> [!WARNING]  
> This also affects the performance data lookup in `parser.ts#L115` which uses `s.name.toLowerCase().trim()` — if two students share a name, only the **first** match is returned, and one student's data is silently lost.

