### BUG-14: `addTeacher` checks `LOWER(username)` for uniqueness, but teachers can share names with students

**File:** [db.ts#L752-L768](file:///c:/Users/panga/OneDrive/Desktop/Seva/SRSMA/SRSMADashBoard/src/lib/db.ts#L752-L768)

The uniqueness check `SELECT 1 FROM users WHERE LOWER(username) = LOWER(${trimmedName})` will prevent adding a teacher if ANY user (student or teacher) has that username. But the unique constraint on the `users` table is `UNIQUE(name, class)`, and teachers have `class = null`. So two teachers could theoretically have the same name (since `NULL != NULL` in SQL), but the code's pre-check prevents it. However, a teacher named "2601" (same as a student's roll number) **would be blocked**, which may be unexpected.

