### BUG-19: Plaintext password comparison is case-sensitive and timing-unsafe  

**File:** [auth.ts#L63](file:///c:/Users/panga/OneDrive/Desktop/Seva/SRSMA/SRSMADashBoard/src/lib/auth.ts#L63)

```typescript
isValid = user.password === credentials.password;
```

For non-bcrypt passwords, this does a direct string comparison. This is vulnerable to **timing attacks** (though low-risk for this app). More importantly, if users set passwords with trailing whitespace, this comparison will succeed, but after a future bcrypt migration, the password may fail (since bcrypt hashing may or may not preserve trailing whitespace depending on the hashing flow).

